Frontend
* A simple web page where users can type and send messages.
* Messages are sent to the backend server.
* The message list updates automatically .

Backend
* Built using Node.js.
* Receives messages from the Backend.
* Processes each message.
* Stores messages temporarily.
* Provides an endpoint to retrieve all messages.


Commands 

1. Update system packages:
Command -->   sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y


2. Install Node.js and npm:
  Command -->  sudo apt install nodejs npm -y

3. Create project directory and move into it:
  Command -->  mkdir Frondend 

   
3.1: Open created new preject directory :
    Command -->  cd Frontend 

3.2.Create the frontend project file::
    Command --> vi My_practice.html

4. Create project directory and move into it:
  Command -->  mkdir Backend 

   
4.1: Open created new preject directory :
    Command -->  cd Backend 

4.2.Create the backend project file::ls

    Command --> vi My_practice.js

5. Initialize Node.js project :
  Command -->    npm init -y

6.and install dependencies:
  Command -->  npm install express cors
  

7. Run the backend server:
 Command -->   node My_practice.js


8. Open frontend page directly :
 Command -->   xdg-open My_practice.html


 Output

* Users can see all sent messages on the web page.
* Each message is shown in Backed.
* The message list updates every 5 seconds automatically.
